<div class="container mt-4">
  <h1 class="mb-3 text-primary">About This Project</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    The <strong>Global Aviation Tracker</strong> is a Ruby on Rails app built to showcase worldwide aviation data.
    It integrates the <em>OpenFlights</em> public datasets : airports, airlines, and routes,  into an interactive, searchable interface.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-secondary">Datasets</h3>
  <ul class="list-group mb-3">
    <li class="list-group-item">airports.csv — name, city, country, IATA, ICAO, latitude, longitude</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">airlines.csv — name, IATA/ICAO, country, active</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">routes.csv — airline, source airport, destination airport, stops</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-secondary">Relationships</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Airline</strong> has many <strong>Routes</strong>, each linking a
    <strong>source Airport</strong> to a <strong>destination Airport</strong>.
    This forms a many-to-many relationship between Airlines and Airports.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-4 text-muted">Built with in Rails using Bootstrap and Leaflet.js for mapping.</p>
</div>
